Linux Checklist for hardening Cyberpatriot machines

To Do:
Finish section 3 - pam


1) Answer the Forensics questions

2) User Auditing
  a) Disable the guest account
    i) go to `/etc/lightdm/lightdm.conf`
    ii) add line `allow-guest=false`
    iii) save the file
  b) Make sure all admins are authorized to be admins
    i) double check this in `/etc/group` 
      ia) group sudo and admin
  c) Delete unauthorized users
    i) save their files

3) Password Auditing
  a) in `/etc/login.defs`
    i) change the lines:
      ```
      PASS_MIN_DAYS *
      PASS_MAX_DAYS *
      PASS_WARN_AGE *
      ```
      to
      ```
      PASS_MIN_DAYS 7
      PASS_MAX_DAYS 30
      PASS_WARN_AGE 14
      ```
    ii) PAM files
      iia) run `sudo apt install libpam-cracklib`
      iib) go to `/etc/pam.d/common-password`
        
        
4) Enable the firewall
  a) install ufw
    i) `sudo apt install ufw`
  b) enable firewall
    i) `sudo ufw enable`
  c) ensure no apps are runnning on the firewall
    i) `sudo ufw app list`

5) IPtables/ports - More to add
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 23 -j DROP         #Block Telnet
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 2049 -j DROP       #Block NFS
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p udp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 2049 -j DROP       #Block NFS
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 6000:6009 -j DROP  #Block X-Windows
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 7100 -j DROP       #Block X-Windows font server
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 515 -j DROP        #Block printer port
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p udp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 515 -j DROP        #Block printer port
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 111 -j DROP        #Block Sun rpc/NFS
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p udp -s 0/0 -d 0/0 --dport 111 -j DROP        #Block Sun rpc/NFS
  sudo iptables -A INPUT -p all -s localhost  -i eth0 -j DROP	       	   #Deny outside packets from internet which claim to be from your loopback interface
  sudo sysctl -n net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies                                 #enable syncookie protection
  echo 0 | sudo tee /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward                        #disable ip forwarding
 
